      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Yes if you only have unit test failures this will make the whole build &quot;look like&quot; it passed with success.  <code>--fail-at-end or -fae</code> should make it continue on and just fail the build at the end, though it also skips dependent modules see <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/12616700/32453\">stackoverflow.com/a/12616700/32453</a>"
